        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 4 at 5:22PM EDT by NWS Wilmington NC</headline>
        <description>At 521 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Lagoon, or 8 miles southeast of Elizabethtown, moving northeast at
30 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Lagoon and White Lake.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
